- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a team of mobile computational entities (agents) cooperating to explore a graph. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper focuses on decentralized exploration. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the solvability and complexity of the graph exploration problem. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is possible as the paper deals with exploring graphs and the agents' interactions with each other. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with mobile agents exploring a graph, which could be relevant to robotics applications.
